items.description:
Appreciate my work? Can you buy me a coffe please :)

Marilyn Monroe: born as Norma Jeane Mortenson; Los Angeles, June 1, 1926-Los Angeles, August 4, 1962) was an American actress, singer, and model. Famous for playing "blonde bombshell" comedic personas, she became one of the most popular sex symbols of the 1950s and early 1960s, as well as an emblem of the sexual revolution of the time. one of the most sought-after actresses for a decade, and her films grossed $200 million (equivalent to $2 billion in 2021) by the time of her death in 1962.6 Long after her passing, Monroe remains a major cultural icon pop.7 In 1999, the American Film Institute ranked her sixth on its list of the greatest female film legends of Hollywood's Golden Age.8 Various film critics and the media have cited Monroe as one of the best actors who never received an Oscar nomination.

items.name: Kawana Misaki (One ~Kagayaku Kisetsu e~)
items.description:
Kawana Misaki from One!

I'm gonna be real, she is the hardest and probably lowest-quality lora I've made so far. I trained TWO different loras. I used as much reference material in the training as I could. But it just keeps wanting to spit out a generic anime girl.

So I'd put her lora weight at 1.2. You have to make sure to add the parted hair and no pupils prompts, and probably add a couple parentheses to make sure it's emphasized. Then you should be able to get a decent rendition going!

items.name: Dark Fantasy Style
items.description:
A Dark fantasy style embedding i made using 24 images to train. Turned out pretty good, and you get results just by using the embedding. No trigger words. Also adding things like: scenery, forest, nature, snow, outdoors, glowing, tree, water, ruins, dark, gives some pretty good results.

The embedding is good for just making sceneries, but works really well with characters. You will kinda get a blend of dark fantasy + your prompt. Have tested it on different models and it works really well on most of them.

Works great with:

CFG Scale: 7-9

Sampling Steps: 20-30

Suggestions for use:

If the face appears to be falling apart, and you want to improve the quality of the face, use Inpaint and Inpaint area use !!only Masked!! (best results) to get a better face, or use Hires. fix to improve, use other seed or tools is also a good way.

Higher resolution (a little higher than 512 * 512) plus Hires. fix, picture quality will be better (if the gpu memory is not enough you can try a Low magnification of Hires. fix or other upscale tools).

Positive prompt for image quality (like best quality) are unnecessary and reduce the possibilities of the picture, also make the picture tend to be in a style.

It's better to Use the weight you would have used for positive quality prompt on negative quality prompt.

If you feel that the content of the picture is not rich enough, You can try to describe in detail to make the picture more closely to your imagination.

The weight of the prompt word and the order in which it is used affects how important it is in the picture.

If there are prompt words that you cannot respond to, please rank the problems in the following order: synonyms (different descriptions of the same concept), prompt word conflicts (positive and negative), model problems (see if other models can respond to the same prompt words), embedding (I am not in the habit of using it, but considering its rationale, I put it up as a reference).

I usually use clip2 when the results don't meet expectations.

Use lora as you like!

items.name: gdhs Style
items.description:
This model is based on anything4.5 trained from the picture of gdhs, and it is recommended to use weights between 0.4 to 0.8.

There have been many controversies about the training and use of art style models, but they are also a difficult part to avoid in the process of AI painting progress.

Therefore, it is recommended to use such art style models as a kind of existence similar to potions, by matching Loras of different art styles with different weights to form images with different styles (although this may lead to bad results, it is worth trying).Alternatively, it can be used to match your favorite character models. Anyway, I hope not to compare it with the artist's own work and make rude remarks, which will harm the community's environment.

At the same time, there are still many problems to be discovered in this model.

In short, hope you have a good time.

items.name: Action body poses
items.description:
I am pleased to tell you that I have added a new set of poses to the collection. This set contains a total of 80 poses, 40 of which are unique and 40 of which are mirrored. Each pose has been captured from 25 different angles, giving you a wide range of options.

Please keep in mind that due to the more dynamic poses, some images may need to be resized to fit your specific needs.

All the images in the set are in png format with the background removed, making it possible to use multiple images in a single scene without worrying about overlapping backgrounds. Additionally, the Controlnet system does not require a background to use the images, so they can be imported as they are.

However, some poses may be too far from the scene and require zooming in for stable diffusion to capture them properly.

Some poses in the set, such as those with extreme angles like top-down or bottom-right upward views, may be challenging for stable diffusion to comprehend without additional prompts support. If stable diffusion is unable to understand or generate these extreme poses, it is advisable to move on to other poses.

theloraprodigy presents

Jago Dibuja LoRA

LoRA trained with theloraprodigy's high quality captioned dataset.

Use 2:3 ratio for best results (e.g. 512x768).


‚ù§Ô∏èLike this model? Support my work by buying me a coffee ‚òï
Commissions also available!

How to use this LoRA model? (AUTOMATIC1111)

  1. Drop the LoRA into the "stable-diffusion-webui/models/Lora" folder and start AUTOMATIC1111. Don't use the standard SD models as they conflicts with the drawing keyword. The URPM checkpoint model works great for example.

  2. Write your prompt as usual in e.g. text2img or img2img but also include "jagodibuja drawing" in the prompt. You can also use danboruu tags (requires danboruu based checkpoint model).

    Example: "woman, jagodibuja drawing".

  3. On the right, under the "Generate" button, click on the button in the center that has an image icon and that says "Show / Hide Extra Networks" when hovering with the mouse on it.

  4. A new section under the prompt will appear, go to the Lora tab there and select this model

Training models requires expensive hardware and is consuming a lot of time. All of my models are free. You can support my work by buying me a coffee ‚òï

Increased species and resolution compared to version 1.0

When using common species such as dogs tiger, cat......, you only need to add the species name without necessarily using a trigger word.
